Upon receipt of a complete Referral Packet, C-YES will:
• send a Registered Nurse to the child’s home or other agreed-upon location to conduct an HCBS eligibility
determination;
• provide Medicaid application assistance to children who are determined eligible for HCBS*;
• submit Medicaid applications, HCBS eligibility determination outcome and support documents, and
capacity updates directly to the Local Department of Social Service (LDSS);
• develop a person-centered HCBS Plan of Care (POC); and
• provide education about Health Home care management.
